ngly well, but that does not mean it comes out unscathed. Still they insert comedy in places that underscore the drama, still they\'d rather emphasize spectacle than emotion, and still do they insist on its audience to seeing all of the MCU films prior because those coming in fresh here would no doubt be lost (most assuredly, most definitely does this film not work as a standalone, but then again, after ten years of this franchise, one wouldn\'t expect it tononetheless a grievous flaw, more machine than human this franchise is, therein lies its Achilles\' heel).\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAt a budget of $300 million, making it one of the most expensive films ever made, Avengers: Infinity War places all that wealth into its effects (which sometimes appear wonky: mostly in the case of Stark or Parker\'s heads appearing incongruous with their digitized suits) and cast, leading to a probability of an abundance of authentic imagination and fervorous filmmaking. Instead, there is palpable lifelessness, a vapidity that has subsumed throughout the entire franchise, and this entry is no different. But there\'s still fun to be had, and I\'m sure those most affectionate toward the MCU deem this extraordinary as they are wholly welcome to dothis is more for them than for me. Bloated, mechanical, and narratively misshapen, but there are hints of pathos and hints of creativity. It\'s fun enough.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n*They\'re not dead. Something something soul stone will bring them all back next timesoul for a soul, right? Plus, Disney likes their money.\r\n\r\n**Thanks Infinity War for reminding me of The Leftovers, and for making Carrie Coon a villainous shrew.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Avengers: Infinity War','','publish','open','open','','avengers-infinity-war','','','2018-05-16 21:42:57','2018-05-16 21:42:57','',0,'http://localhost/?p=159',0,'post','',0),(160,1,'2018-05-16 00:39:52','2018-05-16 00:39:52','','Avengers','','inherit','open','closed','','null','','','2018-05-16 00:40:08','2018-